User Story: As a developer, I want to create REST controllers, so that I can expose the file lead management API.

Acceptance Criteria:

The api module contains the FileLoadController class.

The FileLoadController is annotated with @RestController

The FileLoadController depends on the FileLoadService.

The FileLoadController defines the following API endpoints:

POST/api/file-loads: Creates a new file load (createFileload).

GET/api/file-loads/(id): Retrieves a file load by ID (getFileLoad).

GET/api/file-loads. Searches for file loads (searchFileLoads).

PUT/api/file-loads/[id]/status: Updates the status of a file load (updateFileLoadStatus).

DELETE/api/file-loads/(id): Deletes a file load (deleteFileLoad). POST/api/file-loads/(id)/archive: Archives a file load (archiveFileLoad).

The controllers handle HTTP requests and responses.

The controllers use DTOs for request and response bodies.

The controllers are secured with JWT authentication and authorization (using PreAuthorize).

The controllers include appropriate HTTP status codes.

The controllers are documented with OpenAPI annotations.
